title: Signs point to District 3 antics revving up as race winds down
text:
Photo: Paul Chinn, The Chronicle Aaron Peskin looks on as Alan Leong tapes a campaign poster inside his music shop on Jackson Street in Chinatown in San Francisco, Calif. on Thursday, Sept. 17, 2015. Peskin is seeking to unseat incumbent Julie Christensen in District 3 on the Board of Supervisors, a position he previously held from 2001-2009. Aaron Peskin looks on as Alan Leong tapes a campaign poster inside...
Just a little more than a week to go until election day — meaning all these campaign shenanigans, oddities and head scratchers will soon be over. Here are some updates on the, um, colorful happenings in the city’s most heated race.
